messages.content: ComfyUI-AutoLabel is a custom node for ComfyUI that uses BLIP to generate detailed descriptions of the main object in an image.
What are the key features of ComfyUI-AutoLabel?
The key features of ComfyUI-AutoLabel include generating image to text descriptions, allowing customizable prompts, supporting flexible inference modes, and having an offline mode option.

To install ComfyUI-AutoLabel, clone the repository into your 'custom_nodes' folder in ComfyUI and then install the required dependencies by navigating to the cloned folder and running 'pip install -r requirements.txt'.
What are the steps to add the AutoLabel node in ComfyUI?
To add the AutoLabel node in ComfyUI, start ComfyUI, add the 'AutoLabel' node from the custom nodes list, and connect an image input. Then, configure the parameters as needed.
What parameters can be configured in the AutoLabel node?
The parameters that can be configured in the AutoLabel node include 'image' (required), 'prompt' (optional), 'repo_id' (optional), 'inference_mode' (optional), and 'get_model_online' (optional).
How can you contribute to the ComfyUI-AutoLabel project?
Contributions to the ComfyUI-AutoLabel project are welcome. You can open an issue or submit a pull request with your changes.
What license is ComfyUI-AutoLabel released under?
ComfyUI-AutoLabel is licensed under the MIT License.
What are the acknowledgements for ComfyUI-AutoLabel?
ComfyUI-AutoLabel acknowledges ComfyUI and BLIP as key components or inspirations for its development.
How can you contact the developers of ComfyUI-AutoLabel for inquiries?
For any inquiries regarding ComfyUI-AutoLabel, you can open an issue on the GitHub repository at https://github.com/fexploit/ComfyUI-AutoLabel.
